PART 8: WALLIS PRODUCT — pi FROM EVEN/ODD
======================================================================
  Wallis: pi/2 = prod (2k)^2 / ((2k-1)(2k+1))

  This is a product of EVEN^2 / (ODD * ODD) terms!
  In tournaments: EVEN = Fourier levels, ODD = vanishing levels.
  The even/odd dichotomy of H (all even Fourier, no odd)
  is structurally the same as the Wallis product structure!

  Wallis partial products:
